column5: These pictures are from the Toronto Archives and I found them "INTERESTING"  http://gencat.eloquent-systems.com/webcat/...013_id49320.jpg yonge/dundas pic #1  http://gencat.eloquent-systems.com/webcat/...022_id49412.jpg yonge/dundas pic #2  http://gencat.eloquent-systems.com/webcat/...033_id49545.jpg yonge/gould  http://gencat.eloquent-systems.com/webcat/...019_id49380.jpg brown's sports & cycle-Sam The Record Man  http://gencat.eloquent-systems.com/webcat/...033_id49544.jpg yonge/gerrard  http://gencat.eloquent-systems.com/webcat/...034_id49559.jpg yonge/college
Thanks for sharing a fantastic "blast to the past". Interesting to see, in the third picture, that not much has changed in over 50 years. One guy working and whole bunch watching

I just walked past some of those land marks today! It looks like Yonge and Gerrard hasn't really changed that much! (except for the lack of homeless folks panhandling!) Neat pics and thanks for posting! HH
Forgot to mention, you can see the pictures BETTER if you click the bottom right corner to ENLARGE.
Very cool, thanks for sharing.  Joey
Where's the Walmart?    Enjoyed the pictures!
I always like looking at old pics like that.  Thanks for posting!
